{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a9e6f2f1-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
    "name": "GiGot",
    "description": "End-to-end test collection for GiGot.\n\nFastest setup (matches the shipped environment defaults):\n1. Stop the server.\n2. Run `./gigot -add-demo-setup` — provisions admin `demo` / password `demo-password`, scaffolded repo `postman-demo`, credential `postman-pat`, and prints a subscription token.\n3. Start the server (`./gigot`).\n4. Import this collection + the `GiGot — local` environment, paste the printed token into `subscriptionToken`, hit Run Collection.\n\nAfter you're done, `./gigot -remove-demo-setup` tears the whole thing back down. Everything this collection creates lines up with what the CLI provisions, so the folder structure doubles as documentation of the demo state.\n\nRun the folders in order (or the whole collection with Run Collection) — later requests consume variables captured by earlier ones (subscriptionToken, repoName, headVersion, credentialName, destinationId).\n\nPrerequisites if you're NOT using -add-demo-setup:\n- An admin account exists. Create one with `./gigot -add-admin <username>` and update `adminUser` / `adminPass` in the environment.\n- `auth.enabled = true` in gigot.json if you want the token-scoped requests to actually gate — with auth disabled they all succeed regardless of `subscriptionToken`.\n\nOrdering rules baked into this collection:\n- Admin endpoints (/admin/* and /api/admin/*) use the session cookie set by folder 01 Login. Every admin request overrides collection auth to `noauth` so the bearer isn't sent alongside the cookie (the server's token strategy is tried before session; a bearer-plus-cookie request would authenticate as the token caller and be denied management actions).\n- The repo referenced by the subscription token must exist before the token is issued (see admin.feature: 'Issuing a token bound to a non-existent repo is rejected'). That's why 'Repos — Admin (create)' runs before 'Admin Tokens'.\n- Captured values are written to BOTH the environment and collection scopes so Run-Collection works whether or not an environment is selected.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{subscriptionToken}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:3417" },
    { "key": "adminUser", "value": "alice" },
    { "key": "adminPass", "value": "" },
    { "key": "subscriptionToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "repoName", "value": "postman-demo" },
    { "key": "headVersion", "value": "" },
    { "key": "credentialName", "value": "postman-pat" },
    { "key": "destinationId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "clientId", "value": "postman-client" },
    { "key": "legacyToken", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 Bootstrap",
      "description": "Unauthenticated endpoints. Good smoke-test before touching auth.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "health"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// /api/health is bearer-gated when auth.enabled=true and no token",
                  "// has been issued yet. Accept 401 in that case — the endpoint",
                  "// being reachable at all is what this bootstrap check cares about.",
                  "pm.test('reachable (200 with auth off, 401 with auth on)', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect([200, 401]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('status: ok', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('ok'));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Server pubkey",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/crypto/pubkey", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "crypto", "pubkey"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('pubkey present', () => pm.expect(body.public_key).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Root status page (HTML)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": [""] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('HTML body', () => pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.match(/<html/i));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "01 Admin Session",
      "description": "Cookie-based admin auth for /api/admin/* routes. Postman keeps the gigot_session cookie in its cookie jar for the host, so subsequent admin folders don't need to re-authenticate.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{adminUser}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{adminPass}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["admin", "login"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('session cookie set', () => {",
                  "  const jar = pm.cookies;",
                  "  pm.expect(jar.has('gigot_session')).to.eql(true);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Current session",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/session", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "admin", "session"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "// Use pm.variables.get so environment override wins over collection default.",
                  "pm.test('echoes logged-in admin', () => pm.expect(body.username).to.eql(pm.variables.get('adminUser')));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 Repos — Admin (create)",
      "description": "Admin-only repo lifecycle. Must run BEFORE Admin Tokens so the token's repo allowlist references an existing repo (otherwise /api/admin/tokens rejects it — see admin.feature).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create repo (scaffold Formidable)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{repoName}}\",\n  \"scaffold_formidable\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "repos"] },
            "description": "noauth override → Postman sends only the admin session cookie. POST /api/repos is ActionManageRepos, denied for token callers."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 or already-exists', () => pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('message names the repo', () => pm.expect(body.message || '').to.include(pm.variables.get('repoName')));",
                  "  pm.test('message says scaffolded', () => pm.expect(body.message || '').to.match(/scaffold/i));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 Admin Tokens",
      "description": "Issue / list / rescope subscription keys. The Issue request captures the new token into {{subscriptionToken}} so the bearer-authed folders downstream can use it.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Issue token (saves {{subscriptionToken}})",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{adminUser}}\",\n  \"repos\": [\"{{repoName}}\"]\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/tokens", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "admin", "tokens"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('token returned', () => pm.expect(body.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.test('repos echoed', () => pm.expect(body.repos).to.include(pm.variables.get('repoName')));",
                  "pm.environment.set('subscriptionToken', body.token);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('subscriptionToken', body.token);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List tokens",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/tokens", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "admin", "tokens"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('tokens array', () => pm.expect(body.tokens).to.be.an('array'));",
                  "pm.test('includes ours', () => {",
                  "  const ours = pm.variables.get('subscriptionToken');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.tokens.some(t => t.token === ours)).to.eql(true);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Rescope token (same repo)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"{{subscriptionToken}}\",\n  \"repos\": [\"{{repoName}}\"]\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/tokens", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "admin", "tokens"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "04 Admin Credentials",
      "description": "Outbound credential vault. Every request overrides to noauth so the admin session cookie drives the call — bearer tokens get authenticated first by the server, which would block these as management actions.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create credential",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{credentialName}}\",\n  \"kind\": \"github_pat\",\n  \"secret\": \"ghp_postman_test_dummy_not_a_real_token\",\n  \"notes\": \"Created by Postman collection run\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/credentials", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "admin", "credentials"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 or already-exists', () => pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('name echoed', () => pm.expect(body.name).to.eql(pm.variables.get('credentialName')));",
                  "  pm.test('secret never echoed', () => pm.expect(body.secret).to.be.undefined);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List credentials",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/credentials", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "admin", "credentials"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('credentials array', () => pm.expect(body.credentials).to.be.an('array'));",
                  "pm.test('no secrets leaked', () => body.credentials.forEach(c => pm.expect(c.secret).to.be.undefined));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get one credential",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/credentials/{{credentialName}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "admin", "credentials", "{{credentialName}}"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('kind github_pat', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().kind).to.eql('github_pat'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Rotate credential (PATCH)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"secret\": \"ghp_postman_rotated_still_a_dummy\",\n  \"notes\": \"Rotated by Postman collection run\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/credentials/{{credentialName}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "admin", "credentials", "{{credentialName}}"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('secret still hidden', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().secret).to.be.undefined);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "05 Client Enrollment",
      "description": "Enroll a synthetic client pubkey so the server can seal responses. Re-running with the same client_id + pubkey is idempotent; different pubkey returns 409.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Enroll client",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"client_id\": \"{{clientId}}\",\n  \"public_key\": \"AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA=\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/clients/enroll", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "clients", "enroll"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('client_id echoed', () => pm.expect(body.client_id).to.eql(pm.variables.get('clientId')));",
                  "pm.test('server_public_key returned', () => pm.expect(body.server_public_key).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Re-enroll same key (idempotent)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"client_id\": \"{{clientId}}\",\n  \"public_key\": \"AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA=\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/clients/enroll", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "clients", "enroll"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 (idempotent)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "06 Repos — Read (bearer)",
      "description": "Read-only repo introspection using the subscription token from folder 03. These routes are bearer-gated with per-repo scoping; the token issued above is already allow-listed for {{repoName}}.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List repos",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "repos"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('our repo is in the list', () => {",
                  "  const r = pm.variables.get('repoName');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.repos.some(x => x.name === r)).to.eql(true);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get one repo",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{repoName}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{repoName}}"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Repo status",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{repoName}}/status",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{repoName}}", "status"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Repo branches",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{repoName}}/branches",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{repoName}}", "branches"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Repo log",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{repoName}}/log?limit=10",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{repoName}}", "log"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "10" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "07 Sync — Read",
      "description": "Structured read endpoints. GET /head captures {{headVersion}} so the write folder can use it as parent_version.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Head (saves {{headVersion}})",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{repoName}}/head",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{repoName}}", "head"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('version non-empty', () => pm.expect(body.version).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.environment.set('headVersion', body.version);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('headVersion', body.version);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Tree at HEAD",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{repoName}}/tree",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{repoName}}", "tree"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('files array', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().files).to.be.an('array'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Snapshot at HEAD",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{repoName}}/snapshot",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{repoName}}", "snapshot"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('files base64-encoded', () => {",
                  "  if (body.files.length === 0) return;",
                  "  pm.expect(body.files[0].content_b64).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "File at HEAD (README.md)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{repoName}}/files/README.md",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{repoName}}", "files", "README.md"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 or 404', () => pm.expect([200, 404]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('content_b64 present', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().content_b64).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Changes since HEAD (expect empty)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{repoName}}/changes?since={{headVersion}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{repoName}}", "changes"],
              "query": [{ "key": "since", "value": "{{headVersion}}" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
